      "solution": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">&nbsp;<strong>Ans. C) Niacin deficiency&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Option C:</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\t<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\"><strong>Pellagra </strong>is a clinical condition due to the <strong>deficiency </strong>of <strong>Tryptophan as well as Niacin</strong>.</span></span></span></li>\r\n\t<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Symptoms of pellagra:</span></strong></span></span>\r\n\t<ul style=\"list-style-type:circle\">\r\n\t\t<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Dermatitis</span></strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">: In early stages, <strong>bright red erythema </strong>occurs in <strong>feet, ankles, and face</strong>. <strong>Increased pigmentation </strong>around the neck is known as <strong>Casal&rsquo;s necklace.</strong></span></span></span></li>\r\n\t\t<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\"><strong>Diarrhea</strong>.</span></span></span></li>\r\n\t\t<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\"><strong>Dementia, delirium, irritability</strong>, <strong>inability to concentrate </strong>and <strong>poor memory, ataxia, and spasticity </strong>are seen</span></span></span></li>\r\n\t</ul>\r\n\t</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong><u>Other Options:</u></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>Option A:</strong>&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\"><strong>Riboflavin deficiency: </strong>C/F are limited to <strong>skin and mucous membranes</strong>. It includes <strong>glossitis, magenta </strong>coloured <strong>tongue</strong>, <strong>cheilosis, angular stomatitis and circumcorneal congestion.</strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>Option B:</strong>&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\"><strong>Vitamin B12 deficiency: </strong>&nbsp;Includes <strong>Megaloblastic anemia, Homocystinuria, Demyelination, Subacute combined degeneration and Achlorhydria</strong>.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>Option D:</strong>&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\"><strong>Vitamin C deficiency: </strong>Includes <strong>Scurvy- Gum </strong>becomes <strong>painful, swollen, spongy and loosening of teeth</strong>. <strong>Delayed Wound healing</strong>.<strong> Infantile Scurvy </strong>(Barlow&rsquo;s Disease), <strong>Haemorrhagic tendency-petechiae </strong>and <strong>ecchymoses or hematoma and Weak bones.</strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Educational objective:</span></u></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\"><strong>Pellagra </strong>is characterized by the three Ds: <strong>dermatitis, diarrhea, and dementia </strong>(behavioral disorders). The<strong> skin lesions </strong>typically occur in areas <strong>exposed to sunlight</strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Ref</span></u></strong><strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">: Harper 30/e:&nbsp; p 550, 557, Lippincott 7/e : P 380.</span></strong></span></span></p>",
