      "solution": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Ans. A) Niacin</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Option A:</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\t<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><strong>Pellagra</strong> is a clinical condition due to the <strong>deficiency of Tryptophan as well as Niacin.</strong></span></span></span></li>\r\n\t<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Symptoms of pellagra:</span></strong></span></span>\r\n\t<ul>\r\n\t\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\"><strong>Dermatitis</strong>: In <strong>early stages</strong>, bright <strong>red erythema</strong> occurs in <strong>feet, ankles and face.</strong> <strong>Increased </strong>pigmentation around the<strong> neck</strong> is known as <strong>Casal&rsquo;s necklace.</strong></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n\t</ul>\r\n\t</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cerebellum-web-static.s3.amazonaws.com/media/public/images/2024/04/09/screenshot-2024-04-09-163156.png\" style=\"height:218px; width:300px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\t<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Diarrhea.</span></span></span></strong></li>\r\n\t<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><strong>Dementia, delirium, </strong>irritability, inability to concentrate and poor memory, ataxia, and spasticity are seen</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Explanation:</span></u></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><strong>Option B.</strong>&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><strong>Vitamin C deficiency: (</strong>Includes <strong>Scurvy</strong>- <strong>Gum</strong> becomes <strong>painful, swollen, spongy and loosening </strong>of teeth. <strong>Delayed Wound healing</strong>. <strong>Infantile Scurvy</strong> (Barlow&rsquo;s Disease),<strong> Hemorrhagic tendency-petechiae</strong> and <strong>ecchymoses or hematoma</strong> and <strong>Weak bones.</strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><strong>Option C.</strong>&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><strong>Vitamin B12 deficiency: </strong>&nbsp;Includes <strong>Megaloblastic anemia, Homocystinuria, Demyelination, Subacute combined degeneration</strong> and <strong>Achlorhydria.</strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><strong>Option D.</strong>&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><strong>Riboflavin deficiency: </strong>C/F are limited to<strong> skin and mucous membranes</strong>. It includes<strong> glossitis, magenta colored tongue</strong>, <strong>cheilosis, angular stomatitis </strong>and<strong> circumcorneal congestion.</strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Educational objective</span></u></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">:</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">P<strong>ellagra </strong>is characterized by <strong>dermatitis, diarrhea, </strong>and, if untreated, <strong>dementia,</strong> highlighting the importance of a<strong> balanced diet </strong>and the potential need for<strong> dietary supplementation</strong> in populations<strong> dependent on maize</strong> as a staple food.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><u><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"PT-BR\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Ref</span></u></strong><strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"PT-BR\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">: DM Vasudevan 9/e: p 481.</span></strong></span></span></p>",
